I believe the deis builder is failing to fetch the latest version of the scxml submodule, leaving stale node_modules. I have seen this happen in other projects.

I've tried to set Heroku's NODE_MODULES_CACHE=false, but I'm not sure whether this is supported by deis: https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/nodejs-support#cache-behavior

The only workaround I have found is to delete the module in package.json, and then re-add it. This forces the builder to download the correct module. However, this requires two distinct pushes to deis, doubling build time, and leaves bogus commits in my git history, so it's not an ideal solution.

